1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the characterization of the effective channel distribution and outage probability, which are fundamental concepts in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on ambient backscatter communication systems, which are a type of wireless communication technology. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking): The paper analyzes the outage probability of a communication system, which is a key performance metric in communication and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper provides an exact expression and an asymptotic expression for the effective channel distribution, which can be viewed as a system model. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper deals with a pair of passive tag and reader, which can be viewed as a multi-agent system.
